I was a terrible paper boy, and was terminated after a couple times sleeping in.

@john ezra When I was a paper boy... we had our routes assigned to us... also we had other duties... to collect payment and pay off our bill for the papers (by the 5th of the next month), and try to get new subscribers.

I did it for... 8 years, age 9 to 17.  For the last few years... TV news was starting to reduce subscriptions.  For my first 2 years... just about everybody on the street subscribed.

I was a terrible salesman at getting new subscribers.  But somehow I did the rest... and in retrospect, the most interesting thing was seeing my neighborhood at the same time of day, ever day, for.. what... about 3,000 days in a row.  Divorces, dementia, delinquency... all there on my street.  I set foot in just about everyone's house when collecting their monthly subscription money.  I did a lot of chores like watering and pet care when there were vacations.

